ance":"Montigny-en-Ostervent, Nord, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France","Ittre, Brabant, Belgium":"Ittre, Brabant, Belgium","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Montigny","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Armand, Henri, Jacques, Normand, Remi.","French: habitational name from (Le) Montigny, the name of several places in various parts of France (from a Gallo-Roman estate name, <i>Montiniacum</i>, formed either from a personal name or from a derivative of <i>mons</i> ‘mountain’ + the locative suffix <i>-acum</i>). Compare   Demontigny  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Demontigny","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Aurele, Gilles, Jacques.","French: habitational name, with fused preposition <i>de</i> ‘from’, for someone from any of several places in various parts of France named Montigny (see   Montigny  )."]}]},{"name":"en","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Chinese: variant Romanization of the surname 任, based on its Mandarin pronunciation, see   Ren   1.","Chinese: variant Romanization of the surname 全, based on its pronunciation in Shanghai dialect, see   Quan   2.","Chinese: variant Romanization of the surname 曾, see   Zeng  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Ren","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese Wei, Yong, Hong, Hui, Chuan, Gang, Guang, Jian, Liang, Lihua, Ning, Qing, Chang, Min, Shen, Yiming.","Chinese: Mandarin form of the surname 任, a term for women's rank of peerage in ancient Chinese: (i) it is said that the surname can be traced back to one of the 25 sons of the legendary Huang Di, the ‘Yellow Emperor’ (<i>c.</i> 27th century  BC ). (ii) from Ren (任), the name of an ancient state (located in Renxian in Hebei province) granted to Yu Yang, said to be a son or grandson of the legendary Huang Di, the ‘Yellow Emperor’ (<i>c.</i> 27th century  BC ). His descendants adopted the name of the state as their surname. (iii) from Ren (任), the name of a state (located in Shandong province) during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ).","English: variant of   Renn   2."]}]},{"name":"Eustache","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From Late Greek.  See  <b>Eustace</b> ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"II","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Loving’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Eustache II de Montigny en Ostrvent was born about 1148, in Ittre, Brabant, Belgium, his father, Regnier III de Montigny en Ostrevent, was 35 and his mother, Yolanthe de Roeulx, was 15. He had at least 1 son with Anceline de Rumes. He died in 1186, in Montigny-en-Ostrevent, Nord, Hauts-de-France, France, at the age of 39."},"et":{"about 1148–1186":"umbes 1148–1186","1148–1186":"1148–1186","1150–1196":"1150–1196","1143–1189":"1143–1189","1162–1229":"1162–1229","1115–1182":"1115–1182","1135–1167":"1135–1167","about 1162":"umbes 1162","1143":"1143","1186":"1186","1196":"1196","1162":"1162","1150":"1150","1182":"1182","1115":"1115","1148":"1148","1135":"1135","1167":"1167","1189":"1189","about 1148":"umbes 1148","after 1167":"pä